      "content": "what role? what's the point of playing a part in a tragedy? like, if you know the boat is sinking, \"playing your part\" just means being there until you drown. it actually feels more cruel to keep going, just to watch everything get destroyed. i feel like the only honest way to react to this is to just... stop. to not be part of the cycle anymore. it seems more peaceful than just waiting for the collapse.",
